data:
The planning idea starts from the observation of different social changes and the school is called to respond then: the widespread use among students of information technology in everyday life, a sense of inadequacy of the educational system in the fight against unemployment and early school leavers. Considering these aspects, it is necessary to think of an improvement of the skills of teachers both from the point of view of information technology and teaching methodologies and both  can   avail themselves of the role play, case studies and group work,  in order  to increase the interest of students and contribute to both a reduction of early school leavers and to an improvement of the results of learning of students. It is essential too to think of a system for evaluating the teachers with particular attention to their ability to refresh and remain in line with the times.
The project "A.TE.A.M. FOR INCLUSION - AlTErnative TEACHING METHODS FOR INCLUSION" arises from these considerations and provides a  mobility to 10 teachers in Ireland and 10 teachers in the United Kingdom, in order to realize the experiences of job shadowing for favoring a better social inclusion of students with learning difficulties, i.e. from disadvantaged backgrounds, immigrants or with disabilities, as well as from the need to improve the service of orientation of the students in the labor market.
The objectives of the project are the following ones:
 To guarantee for the teachers more digital skills in order to use the ITC efficiently and effectively in the didactics, helping to mitigate the gap between "native" and "Digital immigrants";
 To Promote, consolidate and reinforce teaching methodologies less traditional such as   CLIL practices, the use of the role play, the study of cases and the work in the group thanks to the experience of the job shadowing; 
 To Share with foreign  schools the effort in combating early school leavers;
 To Create a network of useful partnership for programming new mobilities ; 
To Deepen the  knowledge of the different education systems in particular in the construction of paths of young apprenticeship programmes;
 To Accelerate the path that was already undertaken in the construction of a system of excellence for the evaluation of teachers because of helping raising   the quality of education.
It is intended to promote cooperation between the IISS "D.Romanazzi" and its  planning partners  for the realization of the project’s goals, respectively the British International School (BIS) and Swan  Training Institute, that will be  the stages of preparation of teachers before their mobility , the organization of the logistics  organizational aspects, for the monitoring of the results and their dissemination.
The teachers before departure will receive a linguistic-cultural preparation and they will attend a course based on techniques of according to CLIL methodology (Content and Language Integrated Learning), in order to maximize the effects of mobility. Their results in terms of formation will be constantly monitored both before departure and during the whole period of mobility through reports that the teachers   have  to draw up and  intermediate and final evaluation tests.  From the point of view of results, the project "A.TE.A.M. FOR INCLUSION' will generate results in first place among the teachers that will be directly involved in mobility that will improve their IT and linguistic skills, get new teaching methodologies for the inclusion of disadvantaged young people and/or with learning difficulties. They Will deepen their knowledge of different education systems in Europe and they will broaden their views and increase their spirit of adaptation from the comparison with foreign colleagues, considerably improving the professional curriculum that can boast also experiences and foreign certifications .
During the activities of job shadowing they will  realize   together with foreign colleagues some  material (lecture notes, presentations, ect.) for the realization of didactic activities they will use whe returning from the mobility. 
Through focus groups and meetings, the results of such knowledge will be widespread also among all the staff of "D. Romanazzi" that will be not directly involved in the mobility.
At both local and regional level, the project will provide an opportunity to reflect on the role that the new digital technologies and the use of innovative methodologies that put the learner at the center of the educational process and may represent in order to respond to the challenges that the economic market requires. For the educational world, the project A.TE.A.M. FOR INCLUSION also aims to be an example for  Europe  in order to let  improve itself  and build formative paths of excellence, helping to facilitate the integration and inclusion of many young people, thus lowering the rate of early school leavers.

The current Italian working and education scenario requires, more than ever, a strong reflection on training methodologies and content. The competitiveness of the labor market, the high rate of youth unemployment (15-29 years), particularly in Campania, where it reaches a striking 46% (ISTAT 2014) and the need to be ahead of the competition which has become global, pose new challenges for both students, who are increasingly uncertain about the school to choose and their future, and teachers, called to respond to the changes of our time with updated competences and more effective teaching methods.
The project F.I.D.A.T.I. - Fostering Innovative Didactic and Active Training Initiatives in VET -aims at increasing the skills of ITT "Basilio Focaccia" through collaboration with other European countries, using this opportunity to establish new international partnerships and, at the same time, strengthen the relationship with local companies, with the objective of a constant improvement of teachers and staff competences and, finally, to improve the competences of the recipients of the transmission of knowledge and know-how: the students of the Institute.

The FIDATI project has the following objectives:
1. establishing cooperative relationships with educational institutions (Finland and the United Kingdom) for the exchange of best practices in innovative teaching, through peer learning activities and job shadowing, planned to improve the teaching of vocational subjects of the Institute;
2. acquiring innovative methodologies for the training workshop, encouraging active learning of learners (discovery, action, problem solving);
3. promote and intensify the internationalization of vocational training, enhancing language skills in a second foreign language teachers and encouraging the acquisition of intercultural mediation tools of both the teaching and the administrative staff;
4. strengthening management and IT skills of the Institute staff, through the adoption of methodologies and tools to optimize cost and time management;
5. testing methodologies for the validation of learning outcomes through the application of the quality circle ECVET and the recognition of credits;
6. fostering the creation of national and international networks and strengthening the relationship between professional training and business, encouraging more participation in mobility projects.

Participants will be 20 among teachers and ATA, selected according to the following criteria: motivation; ex-ante evaluation of the candidates competences for mobility and assessment of the possible post-mobility impact level within the Institute.

Main planned activities:
setting up an information desk operated by the project coordinator and a support team (European Mobility Desk - EMD); developing a communication plan of the project; mobility planning; assessment of the candidates competences; identification of individual learning objectives; consultation with the project partners for the attribution of ECVET credits according to learning units; signing the Learning Agreement; provision of preparatory training; phase of mobility: the job shadowing training activities will be carried out from December 2017 to March 2018 as planned (10 participants for Finland and 10 for United Kingdom); validation and certification of credits accrued during mobility; communication and dissemination of results; assessment of educational activities; assessment of the level of effectiveness and efficiency of the administration processes of the Institute; thematic workshops.

Expected results:
- Networking with national and international educational institutions in Finland and the UK;
- Innovation of teaching and methods laboratorial, capacity building and intercultural relationships, use of European instruments such as Europass Language Passport;
- Improving the assessment for the validation of formal, informal and non-formal compentences and testing ECVET for the allocation and transfer of credits;
- Expansion of the management and administrative compentences through the use of ICT tools;
- Consolidation and development of foreign language skills;
- Strengthening of opportunities for professional and career development.
The impact in the short and medium term will cover primarily the teachers and staff participating in the action of mobility, which will improve their teaching and management skills to be activated in their daily practice. It will also create a "cascade" effect: participating teachers and staff will extent among colleagues the results of job shadowing, transferring and systematizing within the management and teaching processes the competences acquired during the period of mobility, in order to increase and harmonize the compentences of the entire staff of the Institute.
